# Getting Started

Use these tips to get up and running quickly:

- [ ] Reach out to [#dev-opslevel](https://your-slack-link.slack.com/archives/example) to join a team
- [ ] Once you've been added to a team, explore [your dashboard](https://app.opslevel.com/dashboard)
- [ ] [Take ownership of your services and Components](https://docs.opslevel.com/docs/getting-started)
  - See [Component Definitions](https://docs.opslevel.com/docs/component-definitions) to understand which Component types to use
- [ ] Check out any [open campaigns](https://app.opslevel.com/campaigns)
- [ ] Add upstream and downstream relationships and dependencies of your Component to quickly see outage, support, and other information in one place
- [ ] Try using the search bar to search for Components, technical documentation, APIs, and more
- [ ] [Link your deployments to OpsLevel](https://docs.opslevel.com/docs/deploys)
- [ ] [Tag your AWS resources](https://docs.opslevel.com/docs/aws-integration) to automatically link them with your Components
- [ ] [Tag your Datadog resources](https://docs.opslevel.com/docs/datadog-integration) to automatically link them to your Components
  - See [Datadog Unified Tagging](https://docs.datadoghq.com/getting_started/tagging/unified_service_tagging/) for more tips on tagging Datadog resources
- [ ] Learn more about OpsLevel at [https://www.opslevel.com](https://www.opslevel.com)





